This documentation is for the Pivotal Cloud Foundry&reg; Dynatrace Ruxit tile.

Dynatrace Ruxit is a smart application performance monitoring solution for highly dynamic and distributed application environments as they run on top of Pivotal Cloud Foundry.

The Dynatrace Ruxit Service Broker Tile includes a Service Broker for Pivotal Cloud Foundry and the BOSH deployment to install the Service Broker on the local PCF installation. The Service Broker will allow Dynatrace Ruxit to be advertised as an add-on service in the Pivotal Cloud Foundry Marketplace, and therefore provision-able and bindable to any app by authorized users within an org. The service broker requires access to an existing Ruxit account which can be configured via the Service Broker's configuration settings. If you do not have a Ruxit account, feel free to sign up for a free trial at: http://www.dynatrace.com/en/ruxit/try-now/


Ruxit automatically detects clustered apps and gives deep visibility into your transaction flows, from the clicks in your users’ browsers to all your communicating microservices, down to the database and code-level for all your monitored apps in Pivotal Cloud Foundry. By means of smartscape technology Ruxit automatically models and adapts real-time dependency graphs of all your pushed apps and connected databases. Whenever Ruxit detects an anomaly in your environment you will be directed to the actual root cause of the anomaly by leveraging the auto-built dependency graphs and all the monitoring data that have been collected. 

### Dynatrace Ruxit Service Broker

A Service Broker allows Cloud Foundry applications to bind to services and consume the services easily from App Manager UI or command line. The Dynatrace Ruxit Service Broker will enable you to use one or more Ruxit environments and is deployed as a Java Application on Cloud Foundry. The Broker exposes the Ruxit service on the Cloud Foundry Marketplace and allows users to directly create a service instance and bind it to their applications either from the Pivotal Apps Manager Console or from the command line. 

The PCF (Pivotal Cloud Foundry) Tile for Dynatrace Ruxit installs the Dynatrace Ruxit Service Broker as an application and registers it as a Service Broker on Cloud Foundry and exposes its service plans on the Marketplace. This makes the installation and subsequent use of Ruxit on your Cloud Foundry applications simple and easy. 

Customers interested in using Dynatrace Ruxit can obtain a 30 day free trial license from Dynatrace Ruxit website.

### Key Features

* **AI Powered**: Don’t spend valuable time hunting for problems, focus on fixing them! Dynatrace Ruxit Artificial Intelligence locates performance issues and pinpoints underlying root causes proactively to ensure customer satisfaction in real time.

* **Analytical**: Discover what you don’t know. Dynatrace Ruxit smartscape technology gives you full operational insight and the ability to oversee and manage web scale applications. 

* **Self learning**: Dynatrace Ruxit automatically learns your environment and understands the complexity of your distributed applications. No more worry about timely troubleshooting. 

* **SaaS convenience with data on-prem**: Keep your data on-premises but get first-class SaaS experience. Dynatrace Ruxit is available as SaaS offering but also as a managed solution on your own infrastructure.


